methods.getSchemaView:
Create a MessageView of the Schema to send as the initial message to a new subscriber.

:param options: (io.deephaven.db.backplane.barrage.chunk.ChunkInputStreamGenerator.Options) - serialization options for this specific view
:param columnNames: (java.lang.String[]) - the names of the columns
:param columnSources: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.ColumnSource<?>[]) - the sources of the columns to capture the types and componentTypes
:param attributes: (java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>) - the table attributes
:return: (io.deephaven.grpc_api.barrage.BarrageStreamGenerator.View) a MessageView that can be sent to a subscriber
methods.newGenerator:
Create a StreamGenerator that now owns the BarrageMessage.

:param message: (io.deephaven.db.backplane.barrage.BarrageMessage) - the message that contains the update that we would like to propagate
:return: io.deephaven.grpc_api.barrage.BarrageMessageProducer.StreamGenerator<io.deephaven.db.backplane.barrage.chunk.ChunkInputStreamGenerator.Options,io.deephaven.grpc_api.barrage.BarrageStreamGenerator.View>
